Python code:
Method 1:
import math
n=int(input())
root=math.sqrt(n+1)
if(int(root)==root):
    print("Sunny Number")
else:
    print("Not Sunny Number")
Output:
48
Sunny Number

Method 2:
import math
n=int(input())
root=math.sqrt(n+1)
if(math.floor(root)==root):
    print("Sunny Number")
else:
    print("Not Sunny Number")
Output:
30
Not Sunny Number

CPP Code:
Method 1:
#include<iostream>
#include<cmath>
using namespace std;
int main()
{
    int n;
    cin>>n;
    double root;
    root=sqrt(n+1);
    if(int(root)==root)
    cout<<"Sunny Number";
    else
    cout<<"Not Sunny Number";
    
}
Output:
48
Sunny Number

Method 2:
#include<iostream>
#include<cmath>
using namespace std;
int main()
{
    int n;
    cin>>n;
    double root;
    root=sqrt(n+1);
    if(floor(root)==root)
    cout<<"Sunny Number";
    else
    cout<<"Not Sunny Number";
    
}
30
Not Sunny Number
